column2: Although this one-piece chamber was not tested, it provided several lessons learned during the design and

column1: development of AM GRCop-84-based combustion chambers. Several features have been modified to mitigate
potential cracking during builds or during post-processing operations. Welding operations for the GRCop-84 were
also developed that allows for future chambers to be welded using EB or TIG. Other design approaches were also
